Islamists are blamed over Beijing blast | The Times
China yesterday blamed an obscure Islamic militant group for a “terrorist” car explosion in Tiananmen Square that left five dead and dozens injured.
Beijing has said that Monday’s attack was carried out by a family of three Uighurs from the western province of Xinjiang. Uighurs are a Muslim minority in a tense region prone to flare-ups of deadly violence.
However, on Friday, the Government’s most senior security official said the attack was a plot by the East Turkestan Islamic Movement — a group whose terror activities are considered by Western diplomats to be exaggerated by Beijing. The Chinese foreign ministry described

